                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.2412 Anti-War/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kaufman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-12T13:00:00-04:32">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 12</hi>[<hi rend="italic">11?</hi>], <hi
                                rend="italic">1928—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 12—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. Bolivia has signed today and delivered to the Legation the multilateral
                    treaty which will be forwarded by pouch.<note n="53a" xml:id="d442fn53a">See
                        despatch No. 58, Oct. 12, 1928, from the Chargé in Bolivia, <ref
                            target="#pg_220">p. 220</ref>.</note> The President and the Acting
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs Palacios requested my presence at the Palace
                    yesterday afternoon and informed me that <pb facs="0807" n="679" xml:id="pg_679"
                    /> Paraguay has violated the mutual understanding in both [<hi rend="italic"
                        >sic</hi>] construction of three forts in disputed territory. Both requested
                    me to notify the Department in the effort to use good influence with Paraguayan
                    Minister in the hope of stopping construction until such time as the matter can
                    be arranged amicably. My answer was that I would convey the foregoing message to
                    the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kaufman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
